# CCNA Home Lab

This repository documents my hands-on networking projects using physical Cisco hardware as I prepare for the CCNA.

## Goals

- Earn the CCNA before returning to Murray State University.
- Strengthen networking fundamentals through practical experience.
- Build a portfolio of documented networking projects.

## Lab Roadmap

- [ ] Lab 001 – VLANs and 802.1Q Trunking
- [ ] Lab 002 – Inter-VLAN Routing
- [ ] Lab 003 – Spanning Tree Protocol (STP)
- [ ] Lab 004 – EtherChannel
- [ ] Lab 005 – Port Security
- [ ] Lab 006 – DHCP Snooping & Dynamic ARP Inspection
- [ ] Lab 007 – Access Control Lists (ACLs)
- [ ] Lab 008 – OSPF Fundamentals
- [ ] Lab 009 – Network Troubleshooting Scenarios
- [ ] Lab 010 – CCNA Enterprise Final Lab

## Hardware

- Cisco WS-C2960S-48TS-S
- Cisco WS-C2960-48PST-S
- USB-to-RJ45 Console Cable
- Cat5e/Cat6 Patch Cables

## About

All configurations and documentation in this repository were created in a personal home lab environment for educational purposes.
